  ✕ Cast of `NaN` to integer
   ╭─[test.lis:5:11]
 4 │ fn main() {
 5 │   let _ = math.NaN() as CountNew
   ·           ───────────┬──────────
   ·                      ╰── `NaN` has no `CountNew` value
 6 │ }
   ╰────
  help: In Go, casting `NaN` to an integer produces an arbitrary, implementation-specific value rather than a meaningful one. Guard with `math.IsNaN(...)` before casting, or keep the value as a float · code: [infer.cast_nan_to_int]
